article.headline: San Jose St. 73, Hawaii 61
article.story: HONOLULU -- Justin Graham scored 19 points to help San Jose State rally past Hawaii, 73-61, in a Western Athletic Conference game Saturday night. Robert Owens and Tim Pierce scored 13 points each and Mac Peterson had 10 for the Spartans (8-8, 2-3 WAC) in the win. Roderick Flemings scored 18 points, Lasha Parghalava and Bill Amis scored 14 each and Kareem Nitoto added 10 for the Rainbow Warriors (9-8, 1-4 WAC). Down 39-34 in the second half, the Spartans used a 19-3 run to take over the game. Graham?s free throw on an intentional foul call gave San Jose State its first lead of the game at 40-39 with 10:30 left. After Hawaii?s Parghalava made a 3-pointer to tie the game at 42, the Spartans scored 11 straight points to lead 53-42 after Graham made two free throws with 7:58 left. The Rainbow Warriors cut the deficit to 53-47 after Amis? two free throws with 6:19 left, but the Spartans went on a 9-1 run to lead 62-48 with 3:06 remaining. Hawaii led 29-25 at halftime.
